    Options o = sc.getOptions();
    o.setTimeOutInMilliSeconds(2000); //2 seconds
    sc.setOptions(o);
    s.setServiceClient(sc);
You can make your calls after setting the above stuff.


  [1]: http://axis.apache.org/axis/java/apiDocs/org/apache/axis/client/Stub.html#setTimeout%28int%29

With axis 1.4 found that actual timeout set from Stub::setTimeout is then appear in SocketFactoryFactory::getFactory, but if the factory for protocol is found in cache, new timeout value is ignored.

Cleaning the cache seems to fix the issue

    stub.setTimeout(10000);
    Map factories = (Map) FieldUtils.readDeclaredStaticField(SocketFactoryFactory.class, &quot;factories&quot;, true);
    factories.clear();

